@ngdoc overview
@name Images
@description

Images are pretty similar to [links](/markdown/links "Links in Markdown"), _except more awesome_! So they need to be preceded by an exclamation mark to show it. By the way, images are great for diving your articles, but you shouldn't abuse them, or they'll feel _shallow_.

```no-highlight
Here's our logo (hover to see the title text):

Inline-style: 
![alt text](http://www.ponyfoo.com/img/thumbnail.png "Inline Title Text")

Reference-style: 
![alt text][logo]

[logo]: http://www.ponyfoo.com/img/thumbnail.png "Reference Title Text"
```

